The paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for recognizing grocery products based on appearance. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes an end-to-end architecture comprising a GAN and a deep CNN, which involves training a generative model and a discriminative model, respectively. This suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with recognizing products based on their visual appearance, which is a task related to multimedia analysis and retrieval, suggesting that it may also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves searching a database of reference images using a K-NN algorithm, which is a task related to information retrieval, suggesting that it may also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
